title: VII EP
text: Chrissy's Debut EP, coined "VII" for the 7 tracks on the EP, 7 Minutes In Hell and for 7 deadly sins.

title: But, What If I Fly?
text: The First Track off VII, heavily inspired by the tale of Icarus, exploring the idea of the fear of the fall versus the dream of the flight.

title: 7 Minutes in Hell
text: The Second Track off VII featuring VOILA 7 Minutes in Hell was the first single released for Chrissy's solo project, contemplating the line between Heaven & Hell.

title: Pick Your Poison
text: The Third Track off VII, one of the most fun to perform live, Pick Your Poison explores a doomed relationship, challenging one's partner to pick how you're going to go out in flames.

title: If Looks Could Kill
text: The Fourth Track off VII, but second single, this was the first song from the solo era that was just Chrissy alone. This track is about an all consuming love.

title: You'd Be Right
text: The Fifth Track off VII, this track is way outside of anything Chrissy has done before but is already a favorite to play live. A little spicier, a step into a dark pop sound.

title: Some Like It Hot
text: The Sixth Track off VII, High energy, lighthearted and fun, Some Like it Hot is purely about finding someone attractive and being too shy to say it!

title: I Tried to Act Your Age
text: The Seventh and final Track off VII, a rare ballad in Chrissy's discography, exploring the regret of trying to grow up too fast.

title: Spin The Bottle Tour
text: The Spin the Bottle Tour, is a coheadline tour between Chrissy and VOILA! Gus & Luke of VOILA co-wrote and produced VII alongside Chrissy, and they have had a blast playing the songs live.

title: Caught It - Performance
text: Chrissy, Luke and Gus had a blast shooting the performance shots for the Caught It music video. It gave a little sneak peak of what the energy for the Spin the Bottle Tour live show would be like!

title: Caught It - Mechanic
text: Caught It was shot in an old mechanic shop set. It only felt right for Chrissy to bust out her leather jacket and give us the mechanic fantasy.

title: Upset Magazine Cover
text: Chrissy graced the cover of Upset Magazine on October 9th. The photographer, Jordan Knight, collabs with Chrissy often and has been a part of the journey for many years

title: G.URL Magazine Cover
text: Chrissy was the cover star for G.url Magazine in September. The fabulous photographer, @coughs, took all the pics for the magazine.

title: Chrissy - "If Looks Could Kill"
text: This photo is from the set of the If Looks Could Kill video, where Chrissy fulfilled her fairytale horseback dreams.

title: Cowgirl Chrissy
text: The era that was always destined to be, Chrissy began riding horses when she was a little girl. At the beginning of 2024, she dove full into being a horse girl and bought her first horse, Leo that April!

title: Starlight Chrissy
text: An organization close to Chrissy's heart, Starlight Children's Foundation aims to bring happiness and smiles to kids who live in the hospital undergoing treatment for extended periods of time. With the help of YOU, Chrissy raised over $56,000 USD to donate to Starlight as a part of Twitch Rivals.

title: Host Chrissy
text: Another one of her many sidequests, catch Chrissy hosting events like Arcane red carpet premieres, Valorant Champions tour and more!

title: DJ Chrissy
text: DJing her first Emo Nite set, Chrissy realized how much fun she had getting to bounce around playing other people's songs. Maybe there's a secret DJ side project in the future?

title: T1 Chrissy
text: Since meeting Faker and the rest of the SKT at Worlds in 2017, Chrissy has been a diehard T1 fan. Her favorite player of all time is Keria and she probably has more T1 jerseys than any other fan.

title: Merch Chrissy
text: Modeling her debut solo merch line for the VII EP! Chrissy wanted each piece to feel like something she would wear, which is why it's mostly black & red, her favorite colors!

title: Sports Chrissy
text: Unfortunately for her, Chrissy is a lifelong New York Giants fan. And though it has been a TOUGH decade (or more, but who's counting!) she has faith and continues to bleed big blue!

title: Chef Chrissy
text: Baking and cooking are the key to Chrissy's heart and she loves to do it with friends or on stream! Her favorite things to make are either Italian dishes or things that feel straight out of a fantasy world.

title: Blonde Hair Chrissy
text: Blondes have more fun! Blonde hair Chrissy says so.

title: Rocksound Cover Mag
text: Rocksound has been a long time supporter of Chrissy and ATC andshe was over the moon getting to create this special edition "Chrissy" mag with them. Shot by Jordan Knight.

title: Bad Idea - Lil Lotus
text: In this feature, Chrissy got to venture outside of her usual sound, as well as shoot an incredibly fun heist style music video with Lil Lotus. The cigarette is real and she did in fact have a coughing fit. Real tough, real cool.

title: Barely Breathing
text: Featuring on Fram Ashes to New's powerful rock track, Chrissy got to land her vocals (and abs) to a new version of the song.

title: A Whole New World
text: The only thing that makes one of Chrissy's favorite Disney songs even more beloved was getting to cover it for Disney's "A Whole New Sound" record with her friends in Yellowcard!

title: Legends Never Die
text: The song that changed Chrissy's life, getting to craft the 2017 Worlds anthem for her favorite game, League of Legends, was a dream come true.

title: You'd Be Right
text: What's better than one Chrissy? Three! And together they make up one full sized person.

title: Perfect Crime
text: Not originally on VII, Chrissy played Perfect Crime on the Spin the Bottle US tour and was the last song written during the VII writing sessions.

title: Pick Your Poison mv
text: The hand at the beginning and end of the visualizer belong to Luke Eisner! He helped out on set that day, and made a small cameo.

title: Phoenix Bilibili Performance
text: To celebrate New Years Eve 2019, Chrissy performed "Phoenix" as a part of Bilibili's celebration broadcast. Complete with a surprise pyro, and floating stage.

title: Duke In "If Looks Could Kill"
text: A very handsome and noble steed! Duke (or Sir Dukers) belongs to Chrissy's trainer, best friend and personal wrangler, Ella! Chrissy learned to ride on Duke before she got her own horse, Leo. Leo & Duke are best buddies.

title: Chrissy in Japan
text: Forever one of Chrissy's favorite places in the world, she frequently travels to Japan and is currently studying Japanese! This photo is just around the corner from her favorite izakaya in Tokyo.

title: Arcane Chrissy
text: Diving into one of her favorite worlds, Chrissy hosted the red carpet for the Arcana Season 1 Premiere as well as the "Undercity Nights" broadcast where this photo was taken.

title: Nerd Chrissy

title: D&D Chrissy
text: Captain Nyxara Nightsbred at your service! Chrissy has been building an original campaign on Dungeons & Dragons 5e called "Starfall" and streamed 6 sessions early 2024!

title: STB Tour Sold Out!

title: The Legend of Hidden Temple
text: Jumping on an open casting call for The Legends of the Hidden Temple reboot, Chrissy and her friend Sigils made the casting director laugh so hard to the point of tears only to be eliminated on the steps of knowledge. Red Jaguars for life!

title: Lando
